Henagar Drive-In has refused to show B&tB because the LeFou character is gay. Here is their statement:
{ "When companies continually force their views on us we need to take a stand." }
 Did they actually say that? They are dictating what their customers can and can not see, and not allowing them to choose for themselves, so essentially they are forcing *their* views on everyone else. Sounds like a double standard to me. How many other sins will they be boycotting at the Henagar Drive-In? I'd better not see anything higher than a 'G' rating being shown there! smh.

So let's recap on this:
*Bill Condon* (_Gods and Monsters_, and _Mr. Holmes_) is going to direct it; 
*Hermione* is playing Belle; 
*Obi-Wan Kenobi* is playing Lumiere; 
*Gandalf* is playing Cogsworth; 
*Nanny McPhee* is playing Mrs. Potts; 
*Otto* from _A Fish Called Wanda_ is playing Maurice (Belle's father); 
*Matthew Crawley* from _Downton Abbey_ is playing the Beast;
*Bard* from _The Hobbit_ films is playing Gaston;
*Olaf* from _Frozen_ is playing Le Fou;
and *Caesar Flickerman* is playing Cadenza;

That's a pretty stellar cast if you ask me.
